of paper currency which had recently been withdrawn from circulation, unbeknownst to Hogue and his accomplices, had been drilled with three holes and rendered worthless.<ref>http://www.vancouversun.com/news/This+week+history+Police+officer+Leonard+Hogue+grisly+murder+suicide+shocked+region/9753959/story.html</ref> Hogue's victims were his wife, Vera (33-34), children, Richard (3), Darlene (4), Clifford (6), Raymond (8), Noreen (12), and Larry (13). <ref>http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/front+page+Vancouver+April+1965+featuring+photos+children+murdered+Vancouver+police+officer+Leonard+Hogue+grisly+murder+suicide+Hogue+also+killed+wife+before+turning+himself+John+Mackie+story/9753960/story.html</ref>\n|-\n|[[Air India Flight 182]]\n|June 23, 1985\n|Atlantic Ocean (WSW of Ireland)\n| 329, of which 268 were Canadians\n| Explosives\n| No\n|Airline bombing of flight originating in Canada, as well as a second failed attack were part of terror plot.  Suspects were eventually tried in Canada, one convicted.\n|-\n|Drinking Party Killings\n|July 29, 1988\n|[[Calgary|Calgary, Alberta]]\n|4\n| Long gun\n| No\n|Russell Rafuse entered a North West Calgary residence and shot 5 people at a party, killing 4.<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/mass-killings-in-canada/article4165424/ |title = Mass Killings in Canada}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://globalnews.ca/news/1272032/stabbing-rampage-among-calgarys-worst-mass-murders/ |title = Calgary's worst mass murders}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[\u00c9cole Polytechnique massacre]]\n|December 6, 1989\n|[[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]\n|15\n| Long gun\n| Yes\n|[[Marc Lepine|Perpetrator]] killed 14 women and injured 14, before taking his own life. School Shooting.\n|-\n|Ontario Glove Factory murders\n|February 3, 1992\n|[[Waterloo, Ontario|Waterloo]], [[Ontario]]\n|3\n| Long gun\n| \n|Patrick Dombroskie shot and killed boss and co-workers.\n|-\n|[[Sydney River McDonald's murders]]\n|May 7, 1992\n|[[Sydney, Nova Scotia|Sydney]], [[Nova Scotia]]\n|3\n| Long gun\n| \n|1 disabled\n|-\n|[[Concordia University massacre]]\n|August 24, 1992\n|[[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]\n|4 / 1\n| Hand gun\n| No\n|School Shooting, 4 killed, 1 injured<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/justice-story/justice-story-college-prof-kills-4-article-1.1320928|title=Crazy professor Valery Fabrikant kills 4 in Concordia University rampage - NY Daily News|last=BOVSUN|first=MARA|work=nydailynews.com|access-date=2018-11-11|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Roger Warren|Giant Mine bombing]]\n|September 18, 1992\n|[[Yellowknife]], [[Northwest Territories]]\n|9\n| Explosives\n| No\n|48-year-old striking gold miner set explosives inside the mine, which killed nine strikebreaking workers.\n|-\n|[[Mark Chahal massacre]]\n|April 6, 1996\n|[[Vernon, British Columbia|Vernon]], [[British Columbia|B.C.]]\n|9\n| \n| \n|Estranged husband murdered wedding party.\n|-\n|[[OC Transpo#1999 Ottawa shooting|OC Transpo massacre]]\n|April 6, 1999\n|[[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]]\n|5\n| Long gun\n| Yes\n|A former OC Transpo employee shot six people, killing four, in a shooting spree at OC Transpo's St. Laurent Boulevard garage, before killing himself. An inquest into the shooting revealed that the shooter had been the subject of bullying.<ref name=Gunman>{{Cite news |title=Gunman opens fire in Ottawa, killing five |url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/1999/04/06/shooting990406.html |publisher=CBC News |date=April 6, 1999 |accessdate=October 15, 2010}}</ref><ref name=Persists>{{Cite news |title=Workplace mistrust persists, 10 years after OC Transpo shooting: driver |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/workplace-mistrust-persists-10-years-after-oc-transpo-shooting-driver-1.848482 |publisher=CBC News |date=April 6, 2009 |accessdate=October 15, 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[W. R. Myers High School shooting|W. R. Myers High School]]\n|April 28, 1999\n|[[Taber, Alberta]]\n|1\n| \n| \n|School Shooting. 1 other injured.\n|-\n|[[Cruse family murders]]\n|June 14, 2002\n|[[Grimsby, Ontario]]\n|5\n| Hand gun\n| Yes\n|Ex-boyfriend Peter Kiss, 30, of [[Milwaukee, Wisconsin]], travelled from U.S. with a [[.45 ACP|.45-calibre]] [[Glock]] pistol and killed his ex-girlfriend, her parents, her 6-year-old child, and himself.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tragedy in Grimsby|url=http://www.niagarathisweek.com/opinion-story/3266374-tragedy-in-grimsby/|publisher=Niagara This Week|accessdate=October 3, 2016|date=June 25, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Penticton Reserve Shooting]]\n|October 30, 2004\n|[[Penticton Indian Band#Indian Reserves|Penticton Indian Reservation]]\n|3\n| Long gun\n| Attempted\n|After drinking 35 beers and snorting cocaine, Dustin Paul shot five friends and relatives while they were all partying at a campsite, killing three of them before slitting his own throat. Claiming in court that he heard a voice telling him to do it, Paul lived to be convicted of three counts of second-degree murder and two counts of attempted murder, and was sentenced to life in prison with the possibility of parole after 16 years.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fong|first1=Petti|title=Penticton murderer recalls hearing voices|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/penticton-murderer-recalls-hearing-voices/article18173237/|newspaper=[[The Globe and Mail]]|accessdate=March 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Killer to serve at least 16 years for shootings on B.C. reserve|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/killer-to-serve-at-least-16-years-for-shootings-on-b-c-reserve-1.685797|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=March 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Mayerthorpe tragedy]]\n|March 3, 2005\n|[[Mayerthorpe, Alberta]]\n|5\n| Long gun\n| Yes\n|James Roszko shot and killed 4 RCMP officers during a property seizure of his farm, he later turned the gun on himself.\n|-\n|Aurora Massacre\n|March 5, 2006\n|[[Aurora, Ontario]]\n|3\n|Blunt force\n| \n|John LaFleche of [[Aurora, Ontario]], beat his two children to death in their beds with a baseball bat \"\"to spare them from becoming wards of the Children's Aid Society\"\" after he murdered their mother earlier that day because he had heard her speaking sexually on the phone with another man.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.thestar.com/news/2008/01/12/man_who_killed_wife_2_kids_with_bat_sentenced_to_life.html |title = Man who killed wife, 2 kids with bat sentenced to life &#124; the Star}}</ref> \n|-\n|[[Shedden massacre]]\n|April 8, 2006\n|[[Shedden, Elgin County, Ontario|Shedden, Ontario]]\n|8\n| Multiple firearms\n| na\n|Gang killing of own gang members.\n|-\n|[[Richardson family murders]]\n|April 22, 2006\n|[[Medicine Hat, Alberta|Medicine Hat]], [[Alberta]]\n|3\n|Shooting\n| No\n|12-year-old girl and her 23-year-old boyfriend killed girl's parents and 8-year-old brother.\n|-\n|[[Dawson College shooting]]\n|September 13, 2006\n|[[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]\n| 2\n| Long gun\n|  \n|School Shooting. \n|-\n|[[Surrey Six murders]]\n|October 19, 2007\n|[[Surrey, British Columbia]]\n|6\n|\n|No\n|Members of a drug gang executed a rival dealer and three of his associates, as well as two innocent bystanders. The resulting violence eventually culminated in the [[2009 Vancouver gang war]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/surrey-six-murder-trial-6-shot-with-heads-covered-1.1871062|title=Surrey Six murder trial: 6 shot with heads covered|publisher=CBC News|access-date=November 23, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-vancouver-gangs30-2009jun30-story.html|title=Drug war on another border: Canada|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|access-date=November 23, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\"\n|-\n|[[Claresholm highway massacre]]\n|December 15, 2011\n|[[Claresholm, Alberta|Claresholm]], [[Alberta]]\n|4\n| \n| Yes\n|21-year-old man shot and killed his ex-girlfriend and two young men who were passengers in the same vehicle.  The man also shot the female driver, before taking his own life.<ref>{{cite web|author1=The Canadian Press|title=Claresholm Highway Murders: Anniversary Of Roadside Shooting That Claimed 4 Lives|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/12/15/alberta-highway-murders-anniversary_n_2308158.html|website=Huffpost Alberta|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=July 5, 2016|date=December 15, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Eaton centre shooting|Eaton Centre Shooting]]\n|June 2, 2012\n|[[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]]\n|2\n| \n| No\n|Gang member open fires in the mall food court as an act of revenge for a former stabbing, killing 2 and injuring 6 others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/christopher-husbands-eaton-centre-shooter-testifies-1.4953465|title=Defence argues Eaton Centre shooter was suffering from PTSD {{!}} CBC News|last=Dec 19|first=Jasmin Seputis \u00b7 Posted|last2=December 20|first2=2018 10:38 PM ET {{!}} Last Updated|website=CBC|language=en|access-date=2019-02-10|last3=2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Danzig Street shooting]]\n|July 16, 2012\n|[[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]\n|2\n| Hand gun\n| No\n|Mass gang shooting at a block party that left 2 dead and 23 injured.<ref name=\"RushCharges\">{{cite news\n|last1= Rush\n|first1= Curtis\n|last2= Poisson\n|first2= Jayme\n|last3= Powell\n|first3= Betsy\n|date= November 8, 2012\n|title= Danzig St. shooting: First-degree murder charges laid in July shootings\n|url= https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2012/11/08/danzig_st_shooting_firstdegree_murder_charges_laid_in_july_shootings.html\n|work= Toronto Star\n|publisher= Toronto Star Newspapers Limited\n|accessdate= June 4, 2017\n|url-status= live\n|archive-url= https://archive.today/20180227162458/https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2012/11/08/danzig_st_shooting_firstdegree_murder_charges_laid_in_july_shootings.html\n|archivedate= February 27, 2018\n}}</ref>\n|-\n|Les Racines de vie Montessori\n|April 5, 2013\n|[[Gatineau, Quebec]]\n| 2\n| Hand gun\n| Yes\n|** Not a massacre by the definition shown at beginning of article.  School Shooting.  Daycare 