{"title_page": "Miss Pennsylvania", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{short description|American beauty pageant}}\n{{for|the state pageant affiliated with [[Miss USA]]|Miss Pennsylvania USA}}\n[[Image:Nicole Brewer.png|thumb|[[Nicole Brewer]], Miss Pennsylvania 2005]]\n\nThe '''Miss Pennsylvania''' competition is the pageant that selects the representative for the state of [[Pennsylvania]] in the [[Miss America]] pageant. Pennsylvania, including early years' city representatives, has won the Miss America crown on five occasions.\n\nOriginally held in [[Hershey, Pennsylvania|Hershey]], the pageant moved to [[West Chester, Pennsylvania|West Chester]] where pageants were held during the 1950s. The pageant was held in [[Altoona, Pennsylvania|Altoona]] from 1974. In 1994, [[Easton, Pennsylvania|Easton]] was chosen as the new venue of the pageant and the date was shifted from June to May. In November 2008, the pageant was moved to the [[Pittsburgh]] area. In 2019, the competition moved to York, PA.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nIn the fall of 2018, the Miss America Organization terminated the Miss Pennsylvania organization's license as well as licenses from [[Miss Florida|Florida]], [[Miss Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], [[Miss New Jersey|New Jersey]], [[Miss New York|New York]], [[Miss Tennessee|Tennessee]], and [[Miss West Virginia|West Virginia]].<ref name=\"Licenses 1\">{{cite news| first=Wayne|last=Parry |url=https://www.apnews.com/f45744999b6a4289aa49c7daa5e43387 |title=Miss America Organization strikes back at rebellious states |work=The Associated Press |date=October 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Licenses 2\">{{cite news| first=Wayne|last=Parry |url=https://www.apnews.com/a60f36cd4af648028b598f48c78f75b9 |title=Miss America terminates agreements with NJ, NY and FL |work=The Associated Press |date=December 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Results summary ==\nThe following is a visual summary of the past results of Miss Pennsylvania titleholders at the national Miss America pageants/competitions. The year in parentheses indicates the year of the national competition during which a placement and/or award was garnered, not the year attached to the contestant's state title.\n\n=== Placements ===\n* '''Miss Americas:''' [[Ruth Malcomson]] ([[Miss America 1924|1924]]), [[Henrietta Leaver]] ([[Miss America 1935|1935]]), [[Rose Coyle]] ([[Miss America 1936|1936]]), [[Frances Marie Burke]] ([[Miss America 1940|1940]]), [[Evelyn Margaret Ay]] ([[Miss America 1954|1954]])\n* '''1st runners-up:''' Roselle Hannon (1941)\n* '''2nd runners-up:''' Linda Olson (1973), Susan Spafford (2000)\n* '''3rd runners-up:''' Barbara Sue Nager (1955), Maureen Wimmer (1972)\n* '''4th runners-up:''' Marion Green (1923), Maggie Walker (1971), [[Tina Louise Thomas]] (1974)\n* '''Top 5:''' Kathleen Coyle (1927)\n* '''Top 10:''' Dorothea Ditmer (1927), Emma Hammermeister (1943), Patricia Hunt (1953), Lois Janet Piercy (1960), Marie McLaughlin (1977), Lynn Carol Grote (1978), Carolyn Louise Black (1980), Michelle Kline (1990), Marla Wynne (1991), Melissa Jeka (2001), [[Nicole Brewer]] (2006), Emily Wills (2007), Katie Schreckengast (2018)\n* '''Top 12:''' Lenore Pollock (1935), Jean McCool (1935), Helen Keaser (1935), Margie Dorie (1944)\n* '''Top 13:''' Gloria Bair (1945)\n* '''Top 15:''' [[Mildred Walker]] (1925), Anna Mae Reefer (1926), Anna Julia Zaker (1936), Bonnie Boyle (1936), Elaine Miller (1936), Kathryn Buckley (1938), Alberta Louise Carts (1940), Mildred Saha (1940), Lillian Handford (1947)\n* '''Top 16:''' Eleanor Kramer (1946), Janice Murray (1951)\n* '''Top 18:''' Geraldine Glassman (1933)\n* '''Top 20:''' Rosalyn Menon (2002)\n\n===Awards===\n====Preliminary awards====\n* '''[[Miss America award winners#Preliminary swimsuit award|Preliminary Lifestyle and Fitness]]:''' [[Evelyn Margaret Ay]] (1954), Emily Wills (2007)\n* '''Preliminary Presentation:''' Rosalyn Menon (2002)\n* '''[[Miss America award winners#Preliminary talent award|Preliminary Talent]]:''' [[Rose Coyle]] (1936), Roselle Hannon (1941), Eleanor Kramer (1946), Jennie Rebecca Blatchford (1958), Lois Janet Piercy (1960), Maureen Wimmer (1972), [[Tina Louise Thomas]] (1974), Lynn Carol Grote (1978), Amanda Smith (2015)\n\n====Non-finalist awards====\n* '''Non-finalist Talent:''' Lorna Malcomson Ringler (1957), [[Judith McConnell|Judith Lynn McConnell]] (1966), Gale Veronica Rothwell (1967), Connie Harness (1976), Lea Schiazza (1986), Linda O'Boyle (1992), [[Candace Otto]] (2004), Rachel Brooks (2008), Kendria Perry (2009), Amanda Smith (2015)\n\n====Other awards====\n* '''[[Miss America award winners#Miss Congeniality|Miss Congeniality]]:''' N/A\n* '''Bernie Wayne Performing Arts Award:''' [[Candace Otto]] (2004)\n* '''Cavalier Scholarship:''' Katarina Sitaris (1988)\n* '''Community Achievement Award:''' Rosalyn Menon (2002)\n* '''Dr. David B. Allman Medical Scholarship:''' Charmaine Kowalski (1979), Shannon Doyle (2010)\n* '''[[Miss America award winners#Quality of Life award|Quality of Life Award]] Winners:''' Michelle Kline (1990)\n* '''Quality of Life Award 2nd runners-up:''' Marla Wynne (1991)\n* '''Roller Chair Parade Third Prize:''' Marion Green (1923)\n* '''Roller Chair Parade Fourth Prize:''' Isabel Lynch (1923)\n\n==Winners==\n{{Plainlist|\n*{{Color box|gold|border=darkgray}} Declared as winner \n*{{Color box|#FFFF66|border=darkgray}} Ended as a runner-up \n*{{Color box|#FFFACD|border=darkgray}} Ended as a finalist or semi-finalist}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%; font-size:90%;\"\n! Year\n! Name\n! Hometown\n! Age\n! Local Title\n! Miss America Talent\n! Placement at Miss America\n! Special scholarships at Miss America\n! Notes\n|-\n|[[Miss America 2020|2019]]\n| Tiffany Seitz<ref>{{cite news |first=Sara |last=Simon |title=Tiffany Seitz, Miss Laurelwood, named Miss Pennsylvania |url=https://www.inquirer.com/news/miss-pennsylvania-tiffany-seitz-20190616.html |work=Philadelphia Inquirer |date=June 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|[[Freeport, Pennsylvania|Freeport]]\n| 23\n| Miss Laurelwood\n| Dance\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n| [[Miss America 2019|2018]]\n| Kayla Repasky<ref name=\"Repasky\">{{cite web|first=Stephanie |last=Sadowski|title= Central Pa. native is now Miss Pennsylvania: Meet Kayla Repasky\n |work=PennLive |url=https://www.pennlive.com/life/2018/06/central_pa_native_is_now_miss.html |date=June 24, 2018}}</ref>\n| [[Gettysburg, Pennsylvania|Gettysburg]]\n| 22\n| Miss Greater Carlisle\n| Contemporary Dance, \"Every Breath You Take\"\n|\n|\n| \n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFACD;\"\n| [[Miss America 2018|2017]]\n| Katie Schreckengast<ref name=\"Schreckengast\">{{cite web| title= Quarryville native Marla Peiffer named first runner-up at Miss Pennsylvania Scholarship Pageant|publisher=Lancaster Online |url=http://lancasteronline.com/news/local/quarryville-native-marla-peiffer-named-first-runner-up-at-miss/article_7be50c02-541c-11e7-a7b6-836eb2c6e5c8.html|date=June 18, 2017}}</ref>\n| [[Palmyra, Pennsylvania|Palmyra]]\n| 20\n| Miss Central Pennsylvania\n| Alto Saxophone, \u201c[[Listen (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Listen]]\u201d from ''[[Dreamgirls]]''\n| Top 10<ref name=\"PA Top 10\">{{cite web|first= Merriell |last= Moyer |url=http://www.ldnews.com/story/news/local/2017/09/12/palmyras-katie-schreckengast-among-top-10-finalists-miss-america-2018/654236001/|publisher= Lebanon Daily News |title=Palmyra's Katie Schreckengast among top 10 finalists at Miss America 2018 |date=September 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| \n| Previously [[Miss Pennsylvania's Outstanding Teen]] 2013<ref name=\"Schreck Teen\">{{cite web|first= Merriell |last= Moyer |title= Palmyra woman crowned Miss Pennsylvania |work= Lebanon Daily News |url= https://www.ldnews.com/story/news/local/2017/06/22/palmyra-woman-crowned-miss-pennsylvania/417942001/ |date= June 22, 2017 |quote=...competed in Miss America\u2019s teen system for four years before eventually winning the title of 2013 Miss Pennsylvania\u2019s Outstanding Teen.}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Miss America 2017|20