america/timeline/timeline2.html |title=Miss America Timeline: 1901\u20131950 |work=[[PBS]]}}</ref></center>\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFACD;\"\n| [[Miss America 1933|1933]]\n| Geraldine Glassman\n|\n| 17\n|\n|\n| Top 18\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1932\n| colspan=8 rowspan=5| <center>No national pageants were held<ref name=\"shut\"/></center>\n|-\n| 1931\n|-\n| 1930\n|-\n| 1929\n|-\n| 1928\n|-\n| rowspan=5| [[Miss America 1927|1927]]\n| Florence Koons\n|\n|\n| Miss Pennsylvania \n|\n|\n|\n| rowspan=5| <small>Multiple Pennsylvania representatives<br><br>Contestants competed under local title at Miss America pageant</small>\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFF66;\"\n| Kathleen Coyle\n|\n|\n| Miss Philadelphia \n|\n| Top 5\n|\n\n|-\n| Mary Millnack\n|\n|\n| Miss Pittsburgh\n|\n| \n|\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFACD;\"\n| Dorothea Ditmer\n|\n|\n| Miss Rochester\n|\n| Top 10 \n|\n|-\n| Esther J. Cantor\n|\n|\n| Miss Wilkes Barre\n|\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=7| [[Miss America 1926|1926]]\n| Name unknown\n| \n|\n| Miss Lancaster\n|\n|\n|\n| rowspan=7| <small>Multiple Pennsylvania representatives<br><br>Contestants competed under local title at Miss America pageant</small>\n|-style=\"background-color:#FFFACD;\"\n| Anna Mae Reefer\n| \n|\n| Miss Philadelphia\n| \n| Top 15\n|\n|-\n| Thelma Williams\n| \n|\n| Miss Pittsburgh\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n| Esther Weissinger\n| \n|\n| Miss Pottsville\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n| Illa Williams\n| \n|\n| Miss Scranton\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n| Helen Villet Grant\n| \n|\n| Miss Wilkes Barre\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n| Name unknown\n| \n|\n| Miss Williamsport\n| \n| \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=9| [[Miss America 1925|1925]]\n|-\n| Annette Jackson\n| \n|\n| Miss Philadelphia\n| \n| colspan=2| <center><small>N/A</small></center>\n| Disqualified for being a professional model\n|-\n| Mary Ann Guth\n| \n|\n| Miss Erie\n|\n|\n|\n| rowspan=8| <small>Multiple Pennsylvania representatives<br><br>Contestants competed under local title at Miss America pageant</small>\n|-\n| Estella Wittell\n| \n|\n| Miss Lancaste